column13: description:{"en":"Living alone as an abandoned princess of the Kingdom of Anzak
column14: I discovered I was in fact in a trashy novel which appeared in my dreams one day. My half-sister was the novel's heroine
column15: while the male lead was well-known to be cruel and heartless. I was just an extra who died before all the drama started. Sold as a scapegoat for the Halvenkia Empire's peace treaty
column17:
unable to escape my fate.

"I'm the only man in Halvenkia who's still single. Don't you fancy me?"

But all of a sudden
column18: the main character wants to marry me. Your first love
column20: and first fling are all with the heroine
column21: but could I take them all for myself?\n\nAlexia
column22: struggling to alter the story in order to survive. Tervion
column23: wanting to keep her all for himself. And Ophelia
column24: the unknown heroine. The original story has now begun to flow in a completely different direction. This is romance fantasy which covers Alexia and Tervion's dreams and fantasies
column25:
as the only ones in each other's eyes.

---

As the bastard child of Anzak's king
column26: Alexia knew she was destined for very little. \"The Book of Wolves\" foretold her destiny as a side character
column27: from her impoverished childhood to her brutal death at the hands of the enemy prince
column28: Tervion. But when Alexia is sent to assassinate him
column29: the story changes. Now she's engaged to him as part of the peace treaty between their two countries. In the face of mortal danger and abandoned by a loveless father in enemy lands
column30:
Alexia must decide where her loyalties lie and whose life matters most.

남주인공은 잔혹하기로 소문 난 황자.그리고 나는 극 시작도 전에 죽는 엑스트라. 하르벤키아 제국의 평화 협정을 위한 희생 양으로 팔려간 나는그렇게 속수무책으로 죽음을 앞두고 있었다.

“하르벤키아에 미혼인 황족은 나 하나라서. 설마 마음에 안 드나?”

그런데 갑자기 남주인공이 내게 결혼을 하잔다.

column9: description:{"en":"Long before the events of Don’t Call Me Dirty
column10: Hanao Kaji and Ryuuji Mita were close friends.\n\nWhen Ryuuji is left to raise his son Shouji as a single father
column11: Hanao steps up to help him out. At first
column12: their family life is happy and content
column13: but Hanao's true feelings for Ryuuji become more and more difficult for him to ignore. The pressure of staying closeted eventually becomes too much to bear; Hanao leaves
column14: choosing to run from his feelings and his fears of somehow “messing up” Shouji’s life when he starts getting teased at school for having two dads.\n\nYears later
